[b]Now we must declare these objects in our object clicking packet to make them work. 
So our action actually happens when clicking on the object.
Therefor open the file where your packets are located. In a normal delta this should be client.java
Search for:[/b] 
[code=java]case 132:[/code]

You should see something like this:
[code=java]
case 132:
			int objectX = inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA();
			int objectID = inStream.readUnsignedWord();
			int objectY = inStream.readUnsignedWordA();
			int face = 0;
			int face2 = 0;
			int GateID = 1;
			if (!validClient)
				break;
			if (!antiHax())
				break;
			if (debug || (playerRights > 1)) {
				println("serverobjs size " + ServerConstants.objects.size());
				println_debug("Object Click: X = " + objectX + ", Y = " + objectY + ", objectID = " + objectID);
			}
			int xDiff = Math.abs(absX - objectX);
			int yDiff = Math.abs(absY - objectY);
			resetAction(false);
			TurnPlayerTo(objectX, objectY);
			updateRequired = true;
			appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
