			}
[/code]


[b]Right under that last bracket add this:[/b]
[code=java]
for (int agilityObject : c.acc.agilityObstacles) {
				if (objectID == agilityObject) {
					c.acc.handleAgilityObstacles(objectID);
				}
			}
[/code]

What we did here is saying:
if the objects id clicked, is an id from the array in our agility class,
then we must check for the action they should execute which is also controlled in our agility class.



[b]Now go to the top of your client class and right under:[/b]
[code=java]
public class Client extends Player implements Runnable {
[/code]

[b]Add this: (this is to call our classes)[/b]
[code=java]
	public AgilityHandler handleagility = new AgilityHandler(this);
	public AgilityCourses acc = new AgilityCourses(this);
[/code]


[b]Now search for this:[/b]
[code=java]
boolean process()
[/code]

[b]In there add this:[/b]
[code=java]
if (handleagility.inGnomeAgility() || handleagility.inBarbarianAgility() || handleagility.inPyramidAgility()) {
			followID = 0;
			if (handleagility.isPassing == true)
				isRunning = false;
			if (absX == handleagility.neededX && absY == handleagility.neededY) {
				handleagility.resetAgility();
			}
		}
[/code]

This checks all the time if the player is in one of the agility areas.
When he is it makes that you can't follow players within that area.
When the player is busy with crossing an obstacle it makes that the player isn't running, so the emote can be properly executed,
and he shouldn't be able to run while crossing an object anyways.
Then when the player is done crossing the objects (when he's on the supposed X and Y coordinate)
it resets agility.

[b]Save and close[/b]



Now we need to do one more thing, this is to make that the player can't start running [b]WHILE[/b] crossing the objects,
for the same reason as above.
[b]Open your clickingMost class and search for:[/b]
[code=java]
case 153:
[/code]

It should look similar to this:
[code=java]
		case 153:
			if (c.playerEnergy > 0) {
				c.isRunning2 = true;
				c.isRunning = true;
			}
			break;
[/code]


[b]Replace it by this:[/b]
[code=java]
		case 153:
			if (c.handleagility.isPassing)
				return;
			if (c.playerEnergy > 0) {
				c.isRunning2 = true;
				c.isRunning = true;
			}
			break;
[/code]

So when the player hits the button to toggle running,
it will check if he's crossing an obstacle. If he is it will not toggle running.




